SUMMARY:Charity Casino Night
LOCATION:522 N Howard Ave Tampa \, FL 33606 United States
DESCRIPTION:Are you looking for a night of excitement that also supports h
 undreds of hospice patients across Hillsborough\, Pinellas\, and Pasco cou
 nties? Mark your calendars! Gulfside Hospice will host its Sixth Annual Ch
 arity Casino Night on Friday\, April 24\, at the Shanna and Bryan Glazer J
 CC in Tampa. This one-of-a-kind event directly supports hospice patients t
 hrough donations and sponsorships\, all while offering thrilling casino st
 yle games such as Blackjack\, Roulette\, Texas Hold Em\, Poker\, slot mach
 ines\, and more. Guests will be immersed in a lively casino atmosphere com
 plete with card tables\, roulette wheels\, delicious bites\, adult beverag
 es\, and a fun photo booth. Whether youre a seasoned poker player or a fir
 st time guest trying your luck\, the evening promises something for everyo
 ne. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/187416
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/187416
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:56649b82-d465-4e53-9fd6-623a7a7470e6
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260324T000706Z
DTSTART:20260424T220000Z
DTEND:20260424T230000Z
SUMMARY:Artist Lecture  Radical Softness: Janet Echelman
LOCATION:120 W Gasparilla Plaza Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a lecture with Janet Echelman\, an artist featured
  in the exhibition Avant Garde: Remarkable Women in the Permanent Collecti
 on. Echelman creates experiential sculpture at the scale of buildings that
  transform with wind and light. The art shifts from being an object you lo
 ok at\, to something you can get lost in. Her work defies categorization a
 s it intersects disciplinary boundaries\, from Sculpture\, Architecture\, 
 and Urban Design to Material Science\, Computer Science\, Engineering\, an
 d Performance. Using unlikely materials from knotted fiber and atomized wa
 ter particles to choreographed dancers\, Echelman combines ancient craft w
 ith original computational design software to create artworks that have be
 come focal points for urban life on five continents. Lectures are offered 
 free with the cost of daily admission: Art Museum Members: Free Not-Yet-Me
 mbers: 25 College Students: Free \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node
 /185961
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/185961
END:VEVENT
